According to a report by Intel Market Research, the global Glass Lined Steel Tank market was valued at USD 1.06 billion in 2024 and is projected to grow from USD 1.12 billion in 2025 to USD 1.55 billion by 2032, registering a CAGR of 5.6% during the forecast period. The market is witnessing steady growth as industries increasingly invest in corrosion-resistant storage and processing equipment capable of handling highly aggressive chemicals while maintaining product purity and operational reliability. Glass lined steel tanks combine the structural strength and durability of steel with the exceptional corrosion resistance of glass, making them an ideal solution for applications in the chemical, pharmaceutical, food & beverage, biotechnology, and energy industries where contamination control and equipment longevity are critical.
